Class Note

java.lang.Object
  Note
Direct Known Subclasses:
NoteDiatonic
public class Note
extends java.lang.Object

A note plays a single frequency. All notes in a song have the same duration. Some notes can be chromatic. A regular music box has 30 notes.

Version:
3.27.2018
Author:
Annabelle Perng

Method Detail

assignNoteName

public java.lang.String assignNoteName(int value)
Given a set note value, assigns a corresponding note name. Note names range from E-3 (highest) to C-0 (lowest). All note values are between 0 and 29, an all note names are exactly 3 characters long.

Parameters:
value - the 'value' of the note, which shows where the note stands relative to the other notes; should be between 0 and 29
Returns:
the formal name of the note, which is a string 3 characters long

compareTo

public int compareTo(Note n)
Compares 'this' note to the parameter object.

Parameters:
n - the note to be compared to
Returns:
< 0 if 'this' object has a higher pitch than parameter object; 0 if 'this' object has the same pitch as parameter object; > 0 if 'this' object has a lower pitch than parameter object.
